{{Infobox video game |title=7 Sins |image=7 Sins.jpg |caption=PAL PC boxart |developer=[[Monte Cristo (company)|Monte Cristo]] |publisher=[[Digital Jesters]] |designer= |engine= |released={{vgrelease|EU|May 27, 2005}} {{vgrelease|TW|22 June, 2005<ref name="ACG">{{cite web|title=罪惡城市：男歡女愛 |url=https://acg.gamer.com.tw/acgDetail.php?s=8676 |publisher=巴哈姆特電玩資訊站 |date=2005-06-22 |accessdate=2018-09-10}}</ref>}} |genre=[[Life simulation game]] |modes=[[Single-player video game|Single-player]] |platforms=[[Windows]], [[PlayStation 2]] }}
'''''7 Sins''''' is a [[life simulation game|life simulation]] [[video game]] where the player must get to the top of the social ladder and make decisions related to the [[seven deadly sins]]. The game is set in the fictional Apple City. Throughout the game the player makes decisions based on [[pride]], [[wrath]], [[greed (deadly sin)|greed]], [[envy]], [[lust]], [[sloth (sin)|sloth]] and [[gluttony]]. Once a relationship has been built new missions are unlocked. In total there are seven chapters and one hundred [[non-player characters]] to interact with.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allgame.com/game.php?id=45757 |title=7Sins - Overview |author= Deci, T.J. |publisher=[[Allgame]] |accessdate=2010-03-10}}</ref>
''[[PC Zone]]'''s staff rated the game 6 out of 10, stating "We can't wholeheartedly recommend 7 Sins as a total gaming experience..",<ref name="pczone">{{cite web |url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=122538 |title=7 Sins Review |author=PC Zone staff |publisher=''[[Computer and Video Games]]'' |date=2005-07-29 |accessdate=2010-03-10}}</ref> but added "... it honestly isn't anywhere near as bad as some might tell you. They're just too timid to admit it."<ref name="pczone"/>
