{{for|the anime studio|Anime International Company}} {{primary sources|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox company | name = Animation International Ltd. | logo = | logo_alt = | image = | image_caption = | type = | traded_as = | ISIN = | industry = | founded = {{Start date and age|1979}} | founders = | hq_location = [[Hong Kong]] | hq_location_city = | hq_location_country = | area_served = Worldwide | key_people = | products = | revenue = | revenue_year = | operating_income = | income_year = | net_income = | net_income_year = | assets = | assets_year = | equity = | equity_year = | num_employees = | num_employees_year = | divisions = | subsid = | website = }}
'''Animation International Ltd.''' is a company headquartered in [[Hong Kong]]. The company was established in 1979 and focuses on film distribution, publishing and licensing.<ref>[http://www.steo.net/download/licensing.pdf Animation International Ltd.] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/69AmRWeoy?url=http://www.steo.net/download/licensing.pdf |date=July 15, 2012 }}</ref> They export and license animation in [[China]], Hong Kong, the [[Middle East]], [[Southeast Asia]] and [[Taiwan]].<ref>Hong Kong Trade Development Council, [http://www.hktdc.com/sourcing/hk_company_directory.htm?locale=en&companyid=1X038KKS Animation International Ltd - Hong Kong] {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/69Amb46J0?url=http://www.hktdc.com/sourcing/hk_company_directory.htm?locale=en&companyid=1X038KKS |date=July 15, 2012 }}</ref> In 1996 they established Animation International (Thailand) Co., Ltd. as a joint venture with JSL Co., Ltd.<ref>[http://www.jslglobalmedia.com/en/animation-international.asp Affiliated Companies Animation International (Thailand) Co., Ltd.] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/69AmliNE9?url=http://www.jslglobalmedia.com/en/animation-international.asp |date=July 15, 2012 }}</ref><ref>HighBeam Research [http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-24643785.html AIT poised to draw up funds from licences, NATION] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/69rdV6OfQ?url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-24643785.html |date=August 12, 2012 }}</ref> The company announced plans to establish places for products related to the [[Doraemon]] franchise in electronics stores and in some [[Laox]] stores as well as a dedicated store which is supposed to open in 2013.<ref>WantChinaTimes [http://www.wantchinatimes.com/news-subclass-cnt.aspx?cid=1502&MainCatID=15&id=20121024000013 Show me the Dorae-money: Cat's popularity not fully marketized] {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6Br7aOC01?url=http://www.wantchinatimes.com/news-subclass-cnt.aspx?cid=1502&MainCatID=15&id=20121024000013 |date=November 1, 2012 }}</ref>
