{{Infobox film | name = Matchless | image = Matchless (film).jpg | caption = | director = [[Alberto Lattuada]] | writer = | starring = [[Patrick O'Neal (actor)|Patrick O'Neal]] | music = [[Gino Marinuzzi|Gino Marinuzzi Jr.]], [[Ennio Morricone]], [[Piero Piccioni]] | cinematography = | editing = [[Franco Fraticelli]] | producer = [[Dino De Laurentiis]] | distributor = | released = 1967 | runtime = | awards = | country = | language = English | budget = }} '''''Matchless''''' (also known as '''''Mission Top Secret''''') is a 1967 Italian [[Science fiction film|science fiction-]][[comedy film]] directed by [[Alberto Lattuada]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Callisto Cosulich|title=I Film di Alberto Lattuada|publisher=Gremese Editore, 1985|isbn=8876051872}}</ref> It parodies the [[spy film]] genre.<ref>{{cite book|last=Adriano Aprà|title=Alberto Lattuada: il cinema e i film|publisher=Marsilio, 2009|isbn=8831797778}}</ref>
== Cast == * [[Patrick O'Neal (actor)|Patrick O'Neal]] as Perry 'Matchless' Liston * [[Princess Ira von Fürstenberg]] as Arabella * [[Donald Pleasence]] as Gregori Andreanu * [[Henry Silva]] as Hank Norris * [[Nicoletta Machiavelli]] as Tipsy * [[Sorrell Booke]] as Colonel Coolpepper * [[Howard St. John]] as General Shapiro * [[Jacques Herlin]] as O-Chin's Doctor
==Reception== In a contemporary review, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' stated that "if audiences are not yet satiated with spy spoofs, United Artists' "Matchless" may get an appreciative reception from the action market."{{sfn|Willis|1985|p=222|ps=: "Review is of 104 minute version reviewed on September 18, 1967"}} The review noted that "the film doesn't take itself too seriously and makes some clever gibes at the expense of military and intelligence powers of all nationalities." and that "uneven acting and technical credits hamper the film's chances of rising above programmer status."{{sfn|Willis|1985|p=222|ps=: "Review is of 104 minute version reviewed on September 18, 1967"}}
